    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i think it might be the soil. how do i check if the pH is the problem and what should i do to fix it if it's too acidic?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To test the soil pH, purchase a pH test kit from your local garden center. Follow the kit instructions to collect a soil sample from your garden and determine its pH level. If the soil is too acidic (pH below 6.0), you can raise the pH by adding lime to your soil. Apply it according to the package instructions, preferably before adding fertilizer, and then re-test the soil after several months to ensure the pH has adjusted properly.",
