    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "how long does it usually take for the lime to actually work? i'm worried the nutrients are getting used up too fast for the lime to keep up.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Lime reactions in the soil can take several weeks to months to fully neutralize acidity. That said, it's important to note that lime compliance can be irregular, as it depends on various factors such as rainfall, temperature, and soil type. If you're concerned about nutrient loss, consider using a slow-release form of lime, or consult with a local extension office for further guidance based on your specific situation. While waiting for the lime to take effect, you can provide your plants with a balanced fertilizer to supply essential nutrients. However, be mindful not to over-fertilize, as this can damage the plants or further lower the soil pH.",
      "source": "target",
